  "text": "Update observation model (Sec. 5.3). [CITATION_1] Figure 3 : Illustrating map maintenance w and w/o compression. After each query video Q finishes, we compress the map by culling known places in Q and combining old places on the map which represent the same place. Thus, the size of transition matrix is shrunk gradually. In contrast, if compression is not conducted, the size of transition matrix will continue increasing. Cull+Combine has comparable inference time while giving better accuracy (see Table 1 ) over No update.",
